Title: The Ten Tests to Determine Whether You Should Be Concerned about Global Warming.
Descript: Presentation by Anthony Watts of http://wattsupwiththat.com/. From DDP 31st Annual Meeting, July 13, 2014, Houston Texas. Anthony Watts is a 25-year broadcast meteorology veteran and currently chief meteorologist for KPAY-AM radio. He got his start as on-air meteorologist for WLFI-TV in Lafayette, Indiana and at KHSL-TV in Chico, California. In 1987, he founded ItWorks, which supplies broadcast graphics systems to hundreds of cable television, television, and radio stations nationwide. ItWorks supplies custom weather stations, Internet servers, weather graphics content, and broadcast video equipment. He also provides weather stations and custom weather monitoring solutions via www.weathershop.com and www.tempelert.com, and turnkey weather channels. In 2007, Watts founded SurfaceStations.org, a Web site devoted to photographing and documenting the quality of weather stations across the U.S. He is the author of Is the U.S. Surface Temperature Record Reliable?

Title: Lord Christopher Monckton: Climate change sceptic in Australia [SD] ABC RN Breakfast
Descript: The Grand Ballroom of Sydney's Sheraton was turning climate change sceptics from the door to hear Britain's Lord Christopher Monckton, in Australia for two weeks to challenge the climate orthodoxy. Underwriting the tour is John Smeed, a semi-retired engineer who's received recognition and many awards for his work over 40 years in the Australian air conditioning and industrial refrigeration industry. Fran talks to Lord Monckton about climate change.

Title: James Delingpole - For: Don't let the eco-warriors ruin your fun - IQ2 debate
Descript: http://www.intelligencesquared.com/ev...James Delingpole arguing for the motion in the IQ2 debate \Don't let the eco-warriors ruin your fun\" at Wilderness Festival on 14th August 2011.He argues that the focus on what's wrong with technology is based on personalities (eg. Jeremy Clarkson) rather than ideas. Ultimately, the varying approaches all strive for a cleaner world - thus we differ in our means, not ends. We have done more harm than good in saving the environment. Wind farms use up rare minerals that are mined immorally, they chop up flying animals, and destroy views. Biofuels could be used in the Third World. A cleaner environment and capitalism go hand in hand, but only if we don't impose artificial barriers."
